{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":984,"text":"All right, let's get up\nour picture of the earth."},{"time":4560,"text":"The earth is pretty awesome."},{"time":6000,"text":"I'm a geologist, so I get\npretty psyched about this,"},{"time":8453,"text":"but the earth is great."},{"time":9840,"text":"It's powerful, it's dynamic,\nit's constantly changing."},{"time":13320,"text":"It's a pretty exciting place to live."},{"time":16280,"text":"But I want to share with you guys today\nmy perspective as a geologist"},{"time":20000,"text":"in how understanding earth's past"},{"time":22240,"text":"can help inform and guide\ndecisions that we make today"},{"time":25760,"text":"about how to sustainably live\non earth's surface."}]},{"cues":[{"time":29520,"text":"So there's a lot of exciting things\nthat go on on the surface of the earth."},{"time":33280,"text":"If we zoom in here a little bit,"},{"time":35360,"text":"I want to talk to you guys a little bit\nabout one of the things that happens."},{"time":39040,"text":"Material get shuffled around\nearth's surface all the time,"},{"time":41800,"text":"and one of the big thing that happens\nis material from high mountains"},{"time":45060,"text":"gets eroded and transported\nand deposited in the sea."},{"time":47560,"text":"And this process is ongoing all the time,"},{"time":49550,"text":"and it has huge effects\non how the landscape works."},{"time":51960,"text":"So this example here in south India --"},{"time":53880,"text":"we have some of the biggest\nmountains in the world,"},{"time":56400,"text":"and you can see in this satellite photo"},{"time":58400,"text":"rivers transporting material\nfrom those mountains out to the sea."},{"time":62600,"text":"You can think of these rivers\nlike bulldozers."},{"time":64800,"text":"They're basically taking these mountains\nand pushing them down towards the sea."}]},{"cues":[{"time":69440,"text":"We'll give you guys an example here."},{"time":71280,"text":"So we zoom in a little bit."},{"time":72640,"text":"I want to talk to you guys\nspecifically about a river."},{"time":75200,"text":"We can see these beautiful patterns\nthat the rivers make"},{"time":77880,"text":"as they're pushing material\ndown to the sea,"},{"time":80000,"text":"but these patterns aren't static."},{"time":81640,"text":"These rivers are wiggling\nand jumping around quite a bit,"},{"time":84350,"text":"and it can have big impacts on our lives."}]},{"cues":[{"time":86340,"text":"So an example of this\nis this is the Kosi River."},{"time":88760,"text":"So the Kosi River\nhas this nice c-shaped pathway,"},{"time":91440,"text":"and it exits the big mountains of Nepal"},{"time":93920,"text":"carrying with it a ton of material,"},{"time":96080,"text":"a lot of sediments that's being\neroded from the high mountains,"},{"time":99070,"text":"and it spreads out across India"},{"time":100950,"text":"and moves this material."},{"time":102560,"text":"So we're going to zoom in to this area"},{"time":104880,"text":"and I'm going to tell you a little bit\nabout what happened with the Kosi."},{"time":108333,"text":"It's an example of how dynamic\nthese systems can be."},{"time":110920,"text":"So this is a satellite image\nfrom August of 2008,"},{"time":114520,"text":"and this satellite image is colored"},{"time":116240,"text":"so that vegetations or plants\nshow up as green"},{"time":118440,"text":"and water shows up as blue."},{"time":120120,"text":"So here again you can see\nthat c-shaped pathway"},{"time":123680,"text":"that this river takes as it exits Nepal."},{"time":126120,"text":"And now this is monsoon season."},{"time":128160,"text":"August is monsoon season\nin this region of the world,"},{"time":130680,"text":"and anyone that lives near a river\nis no stranger to flooding"},{"time":133600,"text":"and the hazards and inconveniences\nat minimum that are associated with that."},{"time":137440,"text":"But something interesting\nhappened in 2008,"},{"time":139720,"text":"and this river moved in a way\nthat's very different."},{"time":142640,"text":"It flooded in a way that's very\ndifferent than it normally does."},{"time":145664,"text":"So the Kosi River is flowing down here,"},{"time":148440,"text":"but sometimes as these rivers\nare bulldozing sediment,"},{"time":151040,"text":"they kind of get clogged,"},{"time":152320,"text":"and these clogs can\nactually cause the rivers"},{"time":154480,"text":"to shift their course dramatically."},{"time":156200,"text":"So this satellite image\nis from just two weeks later."},{"time":159080,"text":"Here's the previous pathway,"},{"time":161040,"text":"that c-shaped pathway,"},{"time":162680,"text":"and you notice it's not blue anymore."},{"time":164800,"text":"But now what we have is this blue pathway"},{"time":166800,"text":"that cuts down the middle\nof the field of view here."},{"time":169280,"text":"What happened is\nthe Kosi River jumped its banks,"},{"time":171640,"text":"and for reference,\nthe scale bar here is 40 miles."},{"time":174360,"text":"This river moved\nover 30 miles very abruptly."},{"time":178560,"text":"So this river got clogged\nand it jumped its banks."},{"time":181760,"text":"Here's an image from about a week later,"},{"time":183880,"text":"and you can see\nthese are the previous pathways,"},{"time":186160,"text":"and you can see this process\nof river-jumping continues"},{"time":188840,"text":"as this river moves farther away\nfrom its major course."}]},{"cues":[{"time":191920,"text":"So you can imagine\nin landscapes like this,"},{"time":194000,"text":"where rivers move around frequently,"},{"time":196640,"text":"it's really important to understand when,\nwhere and how they're going to jump."},{"time":201160,"text":"But these kinds of processes\nalso happen a lot closer to home as well."},{"time":205640,"text":"So in the United States,"},{"time":207480,"text":"we have the Mississippi River\nthat drains most of the continental US."},{"time":211560,"text":"It pushes material\nfrom the Rocky Mountains"},{"time":213960,"text":"and from the Great Plains."},{"time":215520,"text":"It drains it and moves it\nall the way across America"},{"time":218760,"text":"and dumps it out in the Gulf of Mexico."},{"time":221320,"text":"So this is the course of the Mississippi\nthat we're familiar with today,"},{"time":224800,"text":"but it didn't always flow\nin this direction."},{"time":226920,"text":"If we use the geologic record,"},{"time":228600,"text":"we can reconstruct\nwhere it went in the past."},{"time":232120,"text":"So for example, this red area here"},{"time":234440,"text":"is where we know the Mississippi River\nflowed and deposited material"},{"time":238000,"text":"about 4,600 years ago."},{"time":240240,"text":"Then about 3,500 years ago it moved"},{"time":242360,"text":"to follow the course\noutlined here in orange."},{"time":244760,"text":"And it kept moving and it keeps moving."},{"time":246800,"text":"So here's about 2,000 years ago,"},{"time":248720,"text":"a thousand years ago,"},{"time":250440,"text":"700 years ago."},{"time":251680,"text":"And it was only\nas recently as 500 years ago"},{"time":254120,"text":"that it occupied the pathway\nthat we're familiar with today."},{"time":258079,"text":"So these processes are really important,"},{"time":260040,"text":"and especially here, this delta area,"},{"time":262920,"text":"where these river-jumping events\nin the Mississippi"},{"time":266760,"text":"are building land at the interface\nof the land and the sea."},{"time":269600,"text":"This is really valuable real estate,"},{"time":271360,"text":"and deltas like this are some of the most\ndensely populated areas on our planet."},{"time":276640,"text":"So understanding the dynamics\nof these landscapes,"},{"time":279120,"text":"how they formed and how they will\ncontinue to change in the future"},{"time":282280,"text":"is really important\nfor the people that live there."}]},{"cues":[{"time":285480,"text":"So rivers also wiggle."},{"time":287040,"text":"These are sort of bigger jumps\nthat we've been talking about."},{"time":289960,"text":"I want to show you guys\nsome river wiggles here."},{"time":292240,"text":"So we're going to fly down\nto the Amazon River basin,"},{"time":294800,"text":"and here again we have a big river system"},{"time":296840,"text":"that is draining and moving and plowing\nmaterial from the Andean Mountains,"},{"time":301240,"text":"transporting it across South America"},{"time":303080,"text":"and dumping it out\ninto the Atlantic Ocean."},{"time":306560,"text":"So if we zoom in here, you guys\ncan see these nice, curvy river pathways."},{"time":311280,"text":"Again, they're really beautiful,\nbut again, they're not static."},{"time":314280,"text":"These rivers wiggle around."},{"time":316040,"text":"We can use satellite imagery\nover the last 30 or so years"},{"time":319680,"text":"to actually monitor how these change."},{"time":321840,"text":"So take a minute and just watch\nany bend or curve in this river,"},{"time":326040,"text":"and you'll see it doesn't stay\nin the same place for very long."},{"time":329040,"text":"It changes and evolves\nand warps its pattern."},{"time":332840,"text":"If you look in this area in particular,"},{"time":335240,"text":"I want you guys to notice\nthere's a sort of a loop in the river"},{"time":338240,"text":"that gets completely cut off."},{"time":339680,"text":"It's almost like a whip cracking"},{"time":341280,"text":"and snaps off the pathway\nof the river at a certain spot."},{"time":344360,"text":"So just for reference, again,"},{"time":346000,"text":"in this location, that river\nchanged its course over four miles"},{"time":350960,"text":"over the course of a season or two."}]},{"cues":[{"time":353080,"text":"So the landscapes\nthat we live in on earth,"},{"time":356000,"text":"as this material\nis being eroded from the mountains"},{"time":358440,"text":"and transported to the sea,"},{"time":359800,"text":"are wiggling around all the time."},{"time":361440,"text":"They're changing all the time,"},{"time":362920,"text":"and we need to be able\nto understand these processes"},{"time":365400,"text":"so we can manage and live\nsustainably on these landscapes."},{"time":368160,"text":"But it's hard to do\nif the only information we have"},{"time":371240,"text":"is what's going on today\nat earth's surface."},{"time":373600,"text":"Right? We don't have\na lot of observations."},{"time":375680,"text":"We only have 30 years' worth\nof satellite photos, for example."},{"time":380520,"text":"We need more observations\nto understand these processes more."},{"time":383440,"text":"And additionally, we need to know"},{"time":385080,"text":"how these landscapes are going\nto respond to changing climate"},{"time":388320,"text":"and to changing land use"},{"time":389600,"text":"as we continue to occupy\nand modify earth's surface."}]},{"cues":[{"time":393160,"text":"So this is where the rocks come in."},{"time":395720,"text":"So as rivers flow,"},{"time":398240,"text":"as they're bulldozing material\nfrom the mountains to the sea,"},{"time":401160,"text":"sometimes bits of sand and clay\nand rock get stuck in the ground."},{"time":404640,"text":"And that stuff that gets stuck\nin the ground gets buried,"},{"time":407360,"text":"and through time, we get\nbig, thick accumulations of sediments"},{"time":411120,"text":"that eventually turn into rocks."},{"time":413160,"text":"What this means is that we can\ngo to places like this,"},{"time":415760,"text":"where we see big, thick stacks\nof sedimentary rocks,"},{"time":418480,"text":"and go back in time"},{"time":420000,"text":"and see what the landscapes\nlooked like in the past."},{"time":422760,"text":"We can do this to help reconstruct"},{"time":424920,"text":"and understand\nhow earth landscapes evolve."},{"time":430160,"text":"This is pretty convenient, too,"},{"time":431800,"text":"because the earth has had\nsort of an epic history. Right?"},{"time":434800,"text":"So this video here\nis a reconstruction of paleogeography"},{"time":439640,"text":"for just the first\n600 million years of earth's history."},{"time":443280,"text":"So just a little bit of time here."},{"time":445280,"text":"So as the plates move around,"},{"time":448040,"text":"we know climate has changed,\nsea level has changed,"},{"time":451200,"text":"we have a lot of different\ntypes of landscapes"},{"time":454880,"text":"and different types of environments\nthat we can go back --"},{"time":457640,"text":"if we have a time machine --"},{"time":459040,"text":"we can go back and look at,"},{"time":460400,"text":"and we do indeed have a time machine"},{"time":462160,"text":"because we can look at the rocks\nthat were deposited at these times."}]},{"cues":[{"time":465520,"text":"So I'm going to give you\nan example of this"},{"time":467560,"text":"and take you to a special\ntime in earth's past."},{"time":469800,"text":"About 55 million years ago,\nthere was a really abrupt warming event,"},{"time":473040,"text":"and what happened was\na whole bunch of carbon dioxide"},{"time":475560,"text":"was released into earth's atmosphere,"},{"time":477400,"text":"and it caused a rapid\nand pretty extreme global warming event."},{"time":481280,"text":"And when I say warm, I mean pretty warm,"},{"time":483960,"text":"that there were things\nlike crocodiles and palm trees"},{"time":486960,"text":"as far north as Canada\nand as far south as Patagonia."},{"time":490000,"text":"So this was a pretty warm time\nand it happened really abruptly."},{"time":493200,"text":"So what we can do"},{"time":494440,"text":"is we can go back and find rocks\nthat were deposited at this time"},{"time":497520,"text":"and reconstruct how the landscape changed\nin response to this warming event."}]},{"cues":[{"time":501560,"text":"So here, yay, rocks."}]},{"cues":[{"time":503480,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":505840,"text":"Here's a pile of rocks."},{"time":507600,"text":"This yellow blob here,"},{"time":509240,"text":"this is actually a fossil river,"},{"time":511000,"text":"so just like this cartoon I showed,"},{"time":512691,"text":"these are deposits that were\nlaid down 55 million years ago."},{"time":516000,"text":"As geologists, we can go\nand look at these up close"},{"time":519120,"text":"and reconstruct the landscape."},{"time":521240,"text":"So here's another example."},{"time":522760,"text":"The yellow blob here is a fossil river."},{"time":525240,"text":"Here's another one above it."},{"time":526800,"text":"We can go and look in detail\nand make measurements and observations,"},{"time":530120,"text":"and we can measure features."},{"time":531520,"text":"For example, the features\nI just highlighted there"},{"time":533920,"text":"tell us that this particular river\nwas probably about three feet deep."},{"time":537400,"text":"You could wade\nacross this cute little stream"},{"time":539520,"text":"if you were walking around\n55 million years ago."},{"time":542480,"text":"The reddish stuff that's above\nand below those channels,"},{"time":545400,"text":"those are ancient soil deposits."},{"time":547200,"text":"So we can look at those to tell us\nwhat lived and grew on the landscape"},{"time":551080,"text":"and to understand how these rivers\nwere interacting with their floodplains."},{"time":555680,"text":"So we can look in detail\nand reconstruct with some specificity"},{"time":560080,"text":"how these rivers flowed\nand what the landscapes looked like."},{"time":562960,"text":"So when we do this\nfor this particular place"},{"time":566160,"text":"at this time,"},{"time":567400,"text":"if we look what happened\nbefore this abrupt warming event,"},{"time":570160,"text":"the rivers kind of carved their way\ndown from the mountains to the sea,"},{"time":573800,"text":"and they looked maybe similar to what\nI showed you in the Amazon River basin."},{"time":578960,"text":"But right at the onset\nof this climate change event,"},{"time":581440,"text":"the rivers change dramatically."},{"time":583480,"text":"All of a sudden they got much broader,"},{"time":585360,"text":"and they started to slide back and forth\nacross the landscape more readily."},{"time":589880,"text":"Eventually, the rivers reverted\nback to a state that was more similar"},{"time":593800,"text":"to what they would have looked like\nbefore this climate event,"},{"time":597640,"text":"but it took a long, long time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":600240,"text":"So we can go back in earth's time\nand do these kinds of reconstructions"},{"time":604120,"text":"and understand how\nearth's landscape has changed"},{"time":606760,"text":"in response to a climate event like this\nor a land use event."},{"time":610560,"text":"So some of the ways that rivers change"},{"time":612680,"text":"or the reasons that rivers change\ntheir pattern and their movements"},{"time":617480,"text":"is because of things like with extra water\nfalling on the land's surface"},{"time":621440,"text":"when climate is hotter,"},{"time":623400,"text":"we can move more sediment\nand erode more sediment,"},{"time":625960,"text":"and that changes how rivers behave."}]},{"cues":[{"time":628680,"text":"So ultimately,"},{"time":630800,"text":"as long as earth's surface is our home,"},{"time":633440,"text":"we need to carefully manage\nthe resources and risks"},{"time":636840,"text":"associated with living\nin dynamic environments."},{"time":639840,"text":"And I think the only way\nwe can really do that sustainably"},{"time":643800,"text":"is if we include information"},{"time":646040,"text":"about how landscapes evolved\nand behaved in earth's past."}]},{"cues":[{"time":650160,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":651400,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}